<br>
Past a good night Queenie!* laughs*My band decided to make you their Queen and to leave the Amazons in peace but I'll pursue your Nation as long as I'll live.Don't be worried, I'lln't kill you.But I'll leave you there while going to your village and murder your Queen.And you...wait for someone who'll free you from your ties* diabolic laugh*<br>
<br>
* Kiarus rides his horse to Themiskyra while Daphnike tries to free herself.The young warrior remembers that she had hidden a dagger in her right boot.She tries to move her feet and gripping to the tree, she high up her feet to make the dagger fall on the ground.When she successes,she holds the dagger between her feet and begins to cut the ties emprisoning her hands.After she successes,she takes the dagger, cuts the ties emprisoning her feet, put the dagger in her scabbard than range it in her boot, seeks her bow and her horse while seeing that Kiarus killed all the bandits who were loyal to her. She mounts her horse,grabbing the reins with her left hand, her sword with her right one and gallops away to Themiscrya.Skilled horsewoman,Daphnike overtakes him miles north of Sarmatia.<br>
<br>
*The young Amazon warrior draws her sword while pushing a fierce warcry.A fierce,long and bloody combat begins, in a succession of blows and parries. Skilled warrior,Kiarus successes to hit Daphnike's left arm after a long combat and she falls from her horse, losing her sword. She touches her wound, her hand covers by blood.All moves from her body are painful...Kiarus comes down from his horse and puts the end of his sword on Daphnike's throat while saying:*<br>
<br>
It's now your time to die, I never had so much difficulty to kill an Amazon but now, it's your time to meet the Parques and to meet your friend, Areto on the other side.<br>
<br>
* At that time, Daphnike's takes her dagger from her boot and stabs him right in the heart.She saws the warlord fall on the ground, mortally hitten,bleeding profusely and says:*<br>
<br>
Your reign of terror is now ended Kiarus and the Sisters of the Crimson Stone are now avenged.Make your salutations to Hades with my consideration and may the vultures feast on your rotten heart...<br>
<br>
Kiarus: Be...damned...Amazon...be...damned...*he agonizes and dies*<br>
<br>
* Daphnike tears up a piece of the bandit's cloth to make a bandage for her wounded arm.The wound goes down her shoulder and is very long.After taking care of her wound, Daphnike rides her horse to Sarmatia, to visit her athelfi before returning to her homeland, Themiscrya.*<br>
